article.description: Aaron Menzies scored 13 points and grabbed 11 rebounds Monday night to help Seattle hold off Arkansas-Pine Bluff for a 63-58 win.
article.headline: Seattle holds off Arkansas-Pine Bluff 63-58
article.story: SEATTLE -- Aaron Menzies scored 13 points and grabbed 11 rebounds Monday night to help Seattle hold off Arkansas-Pine Bluff for a 63-58 win. Scott Ulaneo and Zach Moore added 12 points apiece for Seattle (5-5), which had to scramble when Arkansas-Pine Bluff erased an eight-point deficit with a 13-2 run that gave the Golden Lions their first lead of the second half, 51-48, with just under six minutes to play. Moore put Seattle back on top, 53-51, with a 3-pointer with 3:09 left but UAPB slipped past the Redhawks one more time with a 5-1 spurt capped by two Jaquan Lynch free throws. Menzies then tied it at 58-all with a dunk with under a minute left and Seattle clinched it with free throws from there. UAPB (1-9), which has lost eight straight, got 12 points from Ghiavonni Robinson, and Lynch finished with 10.
